items.title: S&P 500, Dow hit records, boosted by bank earnings surprise
items.description: The Dow Jones Industrial Average rose 409.74 points, or 0.97%, to 42,863.86, the S&P 500 gained 34.98 points, or 0.61%, to 5,815.03 and the Nasdaq Composite gained 60.89 points, or 0.33%, to 18,342.94.

items.title: Market extends losses for second week; rupee weakens past 84
items.description: The Indian rupee extended the losses and weakened past 84 mark for the first time on Friday.

items.title: Broader indices outperformance continues; more than 50 smallcaps gain 10-28%
items.description: BSE Small-cap and Midcap index added 1 percent each, while Largecap index ended on a flat note.
